Patch notes come in the .rar of the releases.
Check that to see what will be and what has been updated.

Sound/music files should be packed into the .bsp file of the map. Any errors noticed & reported will get worked on.

Periodically, newer versions of the map will come out. (ex. ba_night_out_v2.bsp, etc.)

Please share your feedback and give me some ideas as of what to put into the game! That stuff inspires me!

This map is an underground map.

It has two access ways to the top, one is a security coded door, and one is a secret tunnel from disco.

The door codes for every door are as follows:

1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 9

You will have 3 seconds between each button before it resets itself.

The terrorists start off caged at the back of the base. There are a few hidey-holes for them to creep through.
The ct's spawn in the gun room, which connects to the jailed area through large security doors. There is a working surveillance system near ct spawn that monitors movement through the big security doors.

There is also a working disco, with two custom sounds. The floor of the disco is made up of lights and change colour.

The most handy thing jail break maps don't usually have is the death race room. The death race room can accommodate two terrorists side by side, separated by glass. How it works is, when the terrorists are in position inside the death race chambers. There will be a light count down.
Red
Yellow
Green
On green the terrorists need to run as fast as they can to the end, first one to make it triggers the opponents door to close, and for them to be killed by the trigger_hurt entity.
Simple press of the button and the game resets, ready for the next contestants.

PLEASE LEAVE FEED BACK, AS THIS IS THE FIRST MAP IVE MADE PUBLIC!!

ENJOY!!

This map is based on the idea that what happened if you was in a jungle/forest/outside area. What would it be like. So i created a mud hut jail with inspired natural games.

It came around after playing through the jail maps and realizing that they all are the same, all gray, all blocky, some well done, don't get me wrong, but in the end, very similar. All based inside, and too be honest, i had enough of looking through bars at the boring walls, sometimes, i would change map, and would not notice. Anyway, enough on that rant. How about a Story?

Back Story.
The prisoners were being transported from one facility to another. (as you do). When all of a sudden, a group of tribes people blow out the tires on the prison bus. Before coming on board and slashing out the driver and the guards throat in a blink of an eye. The prisoners had no idea what to do, were these guys worse then the guards?, at least guards had a code to uphold.
Later, the prisoners found themselve being taken through the undergrowth to an area were they can see mudhuts. Once there, they were forced inside, with only a bucket to shit in and the cold wet floor to sleep on, the prisoners were starting to remeber how good prison was to them.
In the mean time, news got out about the hijacked prison bus. The warden immediatly scrambled a jet to their last known location, he took some guards with him to help out. It wasn't long before they found the distinctive mudhuts.
Only, to realise, that his thirst to find them blinded him from his senses, he checked down to see they had run out of fuel. The helicopter plummeted to the floor, only, thats half the problem, they were heading for a cliff face, on the other side, certain death.
[Insert bravery, skill flying, awesome crash]
They made it, from the ruins they got a radio, and scrambled a prison bus to come get them and the prisoners. In the meantime, you have to keep them controlled and entertained.

Minecraft jailbreak map that I made. Few secret teleports (none that you can't find without spectating, though). Fences and ladders are to scale (1 pixel=1 unit). Textures taken from Minecraft, then scaled down in paint and turned into .vtf files by me, though I'm pretty sure others have done it before.

The game with the red-and-white squares is called Spleef. Terrorists are supposed to try and knife out the squares under other Terrorists, making them fall. The button resets 10-ish squares at a time to avoid lagging the server.

Pretty sure the awp is not reachable. It was when I tested the map, but I was on sv_accelerate 10, because it was right after the update changed the default to 5, and I thought it was default :P.

README!
==============
So, you just got ba_mchorrorprison. You're in luck, if you haven't installed a map before!
The instructions for Windows:

1) Locate your Counter-Strike: Source folder. For most people, this is C:\Program Files\Steam\steamapps\*YOURUSERNAMEHERE*\counter-strike source\cstrike\

2) Copy or move the .bsp file (the normal map) into the \maps\ section of that folder. Basically: C:\Program Files\Steam\steamapps\*YOURUSERNAMEHERE*\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps\

3) You're done! There is nothing extra to install, as the extra content is pakratted inside of the .bsp. Enjoy the map!

The instructions for Mac/Linux/Other:

1) Open your web browser.

2) In the address bar, type in "www.google.com"

3) Google how to install on other operating systems. I have no clue how, sorry, I'm a Windows man myself.

You may leave feedback on my Steam profile here, as I'll get the notification: http://steamcommunity.com/id/McBroColi

Also, the license is the default one. You can distribute the work to your friends, but please credit me as the author (and note that a few people have custom textures in the map).
You are not allowed to modify the work in my map and then distribute it as your own. If you would like to help with the map, please get special permission from me on Steam.

_aChangeLog.text: Converted a lot of complex into models for better performance
Added additional sound and music files to games
Made the stop button stop the music as well
Made Hexagon heat larger and more manageable for the CTs, as well as a music change.
Optimised Mari says with model flags instead of Brush. The blank and lettered flags are identical in shape now.
Fixed the gun room spamming issue (deletes the gun if no one picks it up after 0.50 seconds).
Replaced the blue isolation with a doorway into new area
Vastly extended the map (outside area now accessible)
Added 6 new minigames (4corners, shooting range, balloon blow up, small obstacle, dodgeball and large obstacle)
Added a cake room for use in creative play
Added an isolation castle on the outside area

_aLatestUpdates._sText: Special thanks to those in DTK who helped me test the changes.

_sText:
MAJOR UPDATE 11th April 2014

I have made some major changes to the map which include a completely new area, optimization and fixes on existing games etc. Check out the updates section to see a full list.

New games added

4 Corners

Button is pressed and the Ts pick a corner. A corner breaks and those standing on said corner fall and die.

Shooting Range

A 4 slot shooting range with deagles. Ts must shoot their way to the finish to win. Losers are automatically killed.

Obstacle (small and large)

Have added a brand new obstacle course to the map. It has 4 themed stages (summer, snow, desert and castle). The difficulties range in the same manner.

There is also a new small obstacle in the walkway to large obstacle to enjoy.

Balloon Game

A simple game that replicates Bowsers balloon game. Ts press the red and green button continuously until they blow enough air to reach the end.

Dodge ball

A dodgeball with giant yellow ball. Multiple balls can be spawned for additional anarchy.

Cake Room

This is not a game in the normal sense. It was added purely for creative play and allows CTs to make their own games using the cake board. Be creative!

Pictures of maps/changes:

BA_MARIO_PARTY

This is a Jail break map the team and I have been working on for over 6 months. It is our second project completed as a team (after ba_colourful_dtk).

The map theme is, of course, Mario Party.

We have used many custom textures and sounds to really bring out the playfulness of the map and after rigorous testing with the DTK community, we are proud to finally release it!

I will explain a bit about what the map has to offer

General info

The main Cell area has 3 green pipe cells and 6 giant coin boxes as cells. The gun room is fitted with mini coin boxes to allow access to a wide variety of weapons.

There are 2 isolation rooms in this map, 1 next to gun room ramp and 1 near the medical thwomps. When players teleport from a minigame, they end up in the castle isolation room.

On the adjacent room to the cell room, there are 3 "Medical thwomps" that heal. These have a 1/6 chance of crushing you when you walk under them (had a lot of fun with this!).

On the wall opposite the medical thwomps is the gun toss ramp. It looks like coins built up on the wall, but there is an invisible brush allowing antiquate room for players to walk up and toss their guns.

There are 2 doors under the gun room that allow access to the princess' secret room. If you can find the key and guess the invisible button combination, you can access the secret platform.

There are also 3 hidden toad pictures around the map. If you find all 3 toad pictures (reveal them by pressing e) you will enable the hidden minigame (pipe entrance rises up in main cell area).

There is also a spray game on the wall near the Hexagon Heat entrance.

The Mini Games

It wouldn't be a Mario Party map without mini games right?

Well we have replicated some great ones for this map, see the info below!

Hexagon Heat

This game is a great one. Terrorists move onto the coloured tiles while a CT assumes control of the coloured buttons. There is an invisible wall around the game to stop players from jumping out of the game.

When a coloured button is pressed, the players must run to the platform before the rest fall under the lave.

The game gets progressively faster with every push and can be reset using the reset button.

Totem Pole pound

This game is the same one from colourful. It has 4 totem poles for terrorists to race on. The first terrorist to knife the platforms to the button wins the game and gets to choose the fate of his opponents. There is an option to Save, Explode, Drown or Gas them.

Bob-omb Counting

There are 10 terminals for terrorists to use. When the start button is pressed there are a random amount of bombs that spawn for 30 seconds. You must count the bombs and input your guess before the timer runs out.

Losers are teleported into the corner.

Mario Says

This is my personal favorite. The game is the same as Shy guy says. There are 3 marios and 15 platforms in this room.

Terrorists move onto a platform each, or 2 to a platform. When the game starts, the ground will disappear and if you touch the water, you die.

The Marios will hold up a flag every few seconds, and you must press the correct button to stay up. Failure to do so will result in your platform receding into the water.

There are 3 outcomes with the flags. Green-A means you must press the green button, Red-B means you must press the red button, Green or Red (no letter) means you must not touch the buttons.

Game can be stopped at any time.

Platform Peril

This is a simple race game with a twist.

Terrorists move to the start line and when the game begins, they must run and jump as fast as they can to the end.

The platforms still start to fall off as soon as the first player leaves them so try and stay in front.

Winners get to choose 4 cool hats at the end.

Shock Drop or Roll

In this game, terrorists move onto the giant cylinder in the middle of the area. The counter terrorist move into the chamber at the other end and the game begins.

The players must balance on the cylinder while the counter-terrorists have to use arrows to change the direction and trick the terrorists.

The game can be stopped at any time.

There is also a hidden brush that stops players from cheating by jumping.

Hidden Mini Game - Pirate Climb

This game is unlockable by finding the 3 hidden toad stool pictures throughout the map. The pipe will appear in the cell room and players can jump in.

There is a massive pole/ladder in the middle.

When the game starts, boulders will fall on each side, killing you on touch. The objective of the game is to be the first one to the top to win.

Conclusion

I would like to offer a special thanks to all who were involved. I would also like to thank Squall and the DTK community for all their feedback, support and ideas during this project.

If you would like to join a cool gaming community (NOT CLAN) then head on over to www.dying2kill.com.au and join. We are always looking for new dev recruits :)

Enjoy the map!

Note: there is a bug at the tunnels that you get stuck trying to climb the ladder. It will be fixed in betav2

========================================================================================================

The first map I ever made. It was done in 6 weeks from start to finish, with no previous mapping experience. This was exclusively made for a server known as Xtreme Jailbreak, which I teched at the time. Since then, I have left this server, so I'm releasing this map publicly. The map itself is stable even when running on servers taking 50+ players. If anyone experiences any issues with Xtreme Servers saying the map is theirs and theirs alone, you have my permission as the mapper to use this wherever and however you like. They do not own my material.

========================================================================================================

This map although lacking in detail, came to be one of the most enjoyed maps on the server, and is still used to this day, along with many other servers who have stolen it. This release is the official one used on the server and so it includes all the custom banners. 

========================================================================================================

It features:

- Large capacity cell area
- Two floored armory
- Big cage/Tables/Yellow line for control areas
- Kitchen with raising/closing window
- Security Red Room for transport
- Waterpolo
- Diving
- Healing showers
- Tic Tac Toe
- Basketball
- Park
- Theatre
- Obstacle Course
- Castlewars
- Interactive race track
- Control Towers
- Closed gun shop (accessable via exploding car)
- Garage with breakable power box
- Secret weapon via passcoded door
- Disco cell
- Security Sensor Light
- Dodgeball
- Moving spotlights
- Realistic Street environment
- Animated Skybox
- Dual vent system
- Random cell weapon spawner
- Hidden weapons in cells
- Medic & Solitary
- And more.

========================================================================================================

As you can see, this map is packed full of activies and features, and is easily playable and controlable. 

I hope you enjoy it, and make sure you comment on what you think of it.
